LuaFunction.Name: RC_round()
LuaFunction.Description: Rounds floating point input x to p [-6..6] decimal places. Default precision is 0 decimals.
LuaFunction.Formula: function RC_round(x,p) if p == nil then p = 0 end p = math.floor(p) if p < -6 or p > 6 then return "Precision ["..p.."] must be from -6 to 6, cannot format value ["..x.."]",_warning elseif p == 6 then return string.format("%.6f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-6)*1e6)/1e6) elseif p == 5 then return string.format("%.5f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-5)*1e5)/1e5) elseif p == 4 then return string.format("%.4f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-4)*1e4)/1e4) elseif p == 3 then return string.format("%.3f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-3)*1e3)/1e3) elseif p == 2 then return string.format("%.2f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-2)*1e2)/1e2) elseif p == 1 then return string.format("%.1f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-1)*1e1)/1e1) elseif p == 0 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e0)*1e0)/1e0) elseif p == -1 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e1)*1e-1)/1e-1) elseif p == -2 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e2)*1e-2)/1e-2) elseif p == -3 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e3)*1e-3)/1e-3) elseif p == -4 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e4)*1e-4)/1e-4) elseif p == -5 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e5)*1e-5)/1e-5) elseif p == -6 then return string.format("%d",math.floor((x+0.5*1e6)*1e-6)/1e-6) end end

LuaFunction.Formula:

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_getStage()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the current object's from-to stage, or 0000-9999 if stage info is missing
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_getStage() -- Assume stage pattern is: local p = "FAS%d%d%d%d%-%d%d%d%d" if this.layer:match(p) then return this.layer:match(p):sub(-9) else return "0000-9999" end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_getStageFromId()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the from-to stage pattern for the object with given GUID string, or 0000-9999 if stage info is missing
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_getStageFromId(guidString) if guidString == nil then guidString = this.id end if string.len(tostring(guidString)) == 36 or guidString:match("rc") then -- Assume stage pattern is: local p = "FAS%d%d%d%d%-%d%d%d%d" local obj = getObjectFromId(guidString) local lay = obj.layer if lay == nil then return "Object has no layer",_warning elseif lay:match(p) then return lay:match(p):sub(-9) else return "0000-9999" end else return "Bad guidString ["..tostring(guidString).."]",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_stageIntersection()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns stage pattern string as the intersection of two given stage pattern strings of type xxxx-yyyy
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_stageIntersection(ap,bp) local p = "%d%d%d%d%-%d%d%d%d" if ap:match(p) == nil or bp:match(p) == nil then return nil,_warning end a1 = ap:sub(-9,-6) a2 = ap:sub(-4) b1 = bp:sub(-9,-6) b2 = bp:sub(-4) lo = math.max(a1,b1) hi = math.min(a2,b2) if lo >= hi then return "" -- Stages don't overlap else return string.format("%04d-%04d",lo,hi) -- Intersection of stages end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_stageIntersectionFromIds()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns from-to stage intersection between two objects with given GUID strings, or nil if non-overlapping stages

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_getAreaOfType()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the first area of the given variant enclosing the current object (not stage-dependent)
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_getAreaOfType(typeName, guid) local obj = (guid == nil) and this or guid local areas = obj.RcArea:filter(function(x) return x.RCType == typeName end) if (areas.Count > 0) then return areas[0] end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_isInsideOcpArea()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns model check string
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_isInsideOcpArea() areas = RcArea:filter(function(x) return x.RCType == "OCP Area" end) if (areas.Count == 0) then return "Objektet er ikke omsluttet av noen OCP områder", _ok elseif (areas.Count == 1) then return "Objektet er omsluttet av ett OCP område", _ok else return "Objektet er omsluttet av flere OCP områder",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_ocpCode()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the current Operation Control Point (OCP) area's code, or nil if not contained in any OCP area (stage-dependent).
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_ocpCode(guid) local obj = (guid == nil) and this or guid local a = NOBN_getAreaOfType("OCP Area", obj) if a == nil then return "???",_warning elseif NOBN_stageIntersectionFromIds(a.id, obj.id) ~= "" then return a.code else return "???",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_ocpStationRef()

LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_ocpStationRef() area = NOBN_getAreaOfType("OCP Area") return area == nil and "" or area.id end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_axleCounterCode()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a text string DownSection/UpSection for an axle counter sensor
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_axleCounterCode() first = "-" closesDist = math.huge for i = 0, DownSections.count-1 do obj = DownSections[i] if obj.Visible then dist = math.sqrt((obj.geoCoord.X - this.geoCoord.X)^2 + (obj.geoCoord.Y - this.geoCoord.Y)^2) --ignore Z if dist < closesDist then first = DownSections[i].code closesDist = dist end end end second = "-" closesDist = math.huge for i = 0, UpSections.count-1 do obj = UpSections[i] if obj.Visible then dist = math.sqrt((obj.geoCoord.X - this.geoCoord.X)^2 + (obj.geoCoord.Y - this.geoCoord.Y)^2) --ignore Z if dist < closesDist then second = UpSections[i].code closesDist = dist end end end if (MileageIncreasesTowardsLeft == 'True') then first,second = second,first end return first.."/"..second end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_signalNumber()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the number of the signal

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_signalLitra()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the litra of the signal, formated after Bane NORs standard practice
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_signalLitra() local c = tostring(this.Code) if c ~= nil then if c:match("%d+%D+") then return c:match("%d+%D+"):match("%D+") elseif c:match("%D+%d+") then return c:match("%D+%d+"):match("%D+") else return "" end end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_signalName()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the compact name of the signal, formated after Bane NORs standard practice
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_signalName() local c,n,p,m c = tostring(this.Code) n = c:len() p = c:match("%d+") m = (p == nil) and 0 or p:len() if m == n or m == 0 then --Only digit(s) or only letter(s) return c else --Mix of digit(s) and letter(s) return p.."("..c:sub(m-n)..")" end end

(Via)" elseif Variant == "Fiktivt sluttpunkt for togvei" then return t..NOBN_signalName().." (HTv)" elseif Variant == "Fiktivt sluttpunkt for skiftevei" then return t..NOBN_signalName().." LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_signalPartNames() local s = "" if (prop("Hovedsignal") ~= "-") then s = s..prop("Hovedsignal") end if (prop("Forsignal") == "Ja") then s = s.."-Fs" end if (prop("Dvergsignal") == "Ja") then s = s.."-Ds" end if (prop("Middelkontrollampe") == "Ja") then s = s.."-Mk" end if (fromDisplayName("Forsiktig kjøring") == "Ja") then s = s.."-FKs" end if (fromDisplayName("Hovedlinjesignal") == "Ja") then s = s.."-HLs" end if (fromDisplayName("Lysende hastighetssignal") == "Ja") then s = s.."-Hast" end if (fromDisplayName("Høyt skiftesignal") == "Ja") then s = s.."-Z" end if s:sub(1,1) == "-" then s = s:sub(2) end return s end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_balisegruppeID()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns balise group object ID (7 chars)
LuaFunction.Formula:
function NOBN_balisegruppeID() local RM = ReferenceMileage local a if Variant == "Hastighetsbalisegruppe" then a = "-H" elseif Variant == "Signalhøyningsbalisegruppe" then a = "-S" elseif Variant == "Lenkingsbalisegruppe" then a = "-L" elseif Variant == "Sporvekselbalisegruppe" then a = "-V"
elseif Variant == "ETCS L2 balisegruppe" then a = "@" elseif Variant == "Hovedsignalbalisegruppe" then a = "_" elseif Variant == "Forsignalbalisegruppe" then a = "F" elseif Variant == "Repeterbalisegruppe" then if getCollectionLength(Relations["Henter ATC styringsinformasjon fra signal/sporveksel"]) == 0 then return "Rep. mangler styringsinformasjon",_warning end local sig = Relations["Henter ATC styringsinformasjon fra signal/sporveksel"][0] if sig.Relations["Avgir ATC styringsinformasjon til balisegruppe"].count > 1 then b1 = sig.Relations["Avgir ATC styringsinformasjon til balisegruppe"][0] b2 = sig.Relations["Avgir ATC styringsinformasjon til balisegruppe"][1] if b1.id == this.id then else b1 = sig.Relations["Avgir ATC styringsinformasjon til balisegruppe"][1] b2 = sig.Relations["Avgir ATC styringsinformasjon til balisegruppe"][0] end if math.abs(b1.ReferenceMileage-sig.ReferenceMileage) < math.abs(b2.ReferenceMileage-sig.ReferenceMileage) then a = "U" else a = "R" end else a = "R" end end
if Variant == "Hastighetsbalisegruppe" then r = Relations["Har bremsekurve målpunkt i balisegruppe"] if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then --Group is braking curve target: ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(this) else --Warning board, use target's ocp: ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(r[0]) end return ocp..a..string.format("%02d",seq)
elseif Variant == "Signalhøyningsbalisegruppe" or Variant == "Sporvekselbalisegruppe" then ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(this) return ocp..a..string.format("%02d",seq)
elseif Variant =="Lenkingsbalisegruppe" then r = Relations["Lenker til balisegruppe"] if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(this) else ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(r[0]) end return ocp..a..string.format("%02d",seq)
else local r = Relations["Henter ATC styringsinformasjon fra signal/sporveksel"] if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then return "Mangler styringsinformasjon",_warning else --Assume r[0] holds object dictating the group's number: ocp = NOBN_ocpCode(r[0]) if r[0].code == nil then return ocp..a.."???",_warning elseif tostring(r[0].code):match("%d+") == nil then return ocp..a.."???",_warning else return ocp..a..tostring(r[0].code):match("%d+"):sub(-3) end end return ocp..a..code:match("%d+"):sub(-3) end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseTekstOver()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns text code over balise symbol according to BN practice
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseTekstOver() local r = Relations["Tilhører balisegruppe"] if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then return "g?" else local g = r[0] t = code:sub(-1) if g.Variant == "Hastighetsbalisegruppe" then if t == "A" then return "H" elseif t == "B" then if Variant:match("Fylt") then return "H" else return "" end elseif t == "C" then return "" else return "?",_warning end elseif g.Variant == "ET-balisegruppe" then if t == "A" then return "EH" elseif t == "B" then if Variant:match("Fylt") then return "EH" else return "" end elseif t == "C" then return "" else return "?",_warning end elseif code:sub(-1) == "P" then return "P" else return "" end end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseID()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns unique balise ID code (8 chars) according to BN practice
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseID() -- SA-ATB@code -- 2018-05-03 MARUF/CLFEY Adjustments. -- 2018-04-26 MARUF Created. -- local r = Relations["Tilhører balisegruppe"] if getCollectionLength(r) == 0 then return "Dangling balise",_warning else g = r[0] end if g.dir ~= "up" and g.dir ~= "down" then return "Bad direction ["..g.dir.."]",_warning end if getCollectionLength(g.Relations["Har posisjonsdefinerende balise"]) == 0 then return "No A-balise in balise group - cannot determine balise type",_warning else isA = (getCollectionLength(Relations["Definerer posisjon for balisegruppe"]) == 1) siblings = g.Relations["Inneholder balise"] a = g.Relations["Har posisjonsdefinerende balise"][0] n = getCollectionLength(siblings) end if isA == true then suffix = "A" else if n == 2 then suffix = "B" elseif n > 2 then Pbalise={id=0, diff=math.huge} Bbalise={id=0, diff=math.huge} Cbalise={id=0, diff=math.huge} for i = 0, n-1 do diff = (g.dir == "up") and (siblings[i].ReferenceMileage - a.ReferenceMileage) or (a.ReferenceMileage - siblings[i].ReferenceMileage) if (diff < 0) then if Pbalise.id == 0 then Pbalise.id = siblings[i].id Pbalise.diff = diff elseif Pbalise.diff > diff then Pbalise.id = siblings[i].id Pbalise.diff = diff end elseif (diff > 0) then if Bbalise.id == 0 then Bbalise.id = siblings[i].id Bbalise.diff = diff elseif Bbalise.diff > diff then Cbalise.id = Bbalise.id Cbalise.diff = Bbalise.diff Bbalise.id = siblings[i].id Bbalise.diff = diff elseif Cbalise.diff > diff then Cbalise.id = siblings[i].id Cbalise.diff = diff end else --diff==0: Do nothing end end if this.id == Bbalise.id then suffix = "B" elseif this.id == Cbalise.id then suffix = "C" elseif this.id == Pbalise.id then suffix = "P" else suffix = "Bad balise group configuration - cannot determine PABC type",_warning end end end return g.name..suffix end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseOffset3DZ()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns balise 3D vertical offset due to track cant
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseOffset3DZ() --Lift (half of superelevation(cant) in center track) c = getAlignmentInfo().cant if NOBN_isNan(c) then return 0,_warning else -- Assume only one rail lifted at a time. CantRotation cw/ccw doesn’t matter. return (c/1000.0)/2 end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseDistanceToNextBalise()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks distance to next balise (higher mileage)
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseDistanceToNextBalise() nextBalise = getUpObject(RCType) if (nextBalise == nil) then return "Ingen baliser i kjørbar forbindelse i stigende km", _ok end local dist = distance(nextBalise) local distOut = string.format("%.3f", dist) if (dist < 2.35 ) then return distOut..": Ugyldig – Balisenes magnetfelt kan flyte sammen – øk avstand", {nextBalise},_error elseif (dist >= 2.35 and dist < 2.8) then return distOut..": Advarsel – Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – øk avstand", {nextBalise},_warning elseif (dist >= 2.8 and dist < 3.2) then return distOut..": OK – Toget vil med god margin plassere balisene i samme gruppe", {nextBalise},_ok elseif (dist >= 3.2 and dist < 3.5) then return distOut..": Advarsel – Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – senk avstand", {nextBalise},_warning elseif (dist >= 3.5 and dist < 10.5) then return distOut..": Ugyldig – Toget kan ikke entydig avgjøre balisenes gruppetilhørighet", {nextBalise},_error elseif (dist >= 10.5 and dist < 11.8) then return distOut..": Advarsel – Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – øk avstand", {nextBalise},_warning elseif (dist > 11.8) then return distOut..": OK – Toget vil med god margin plassere balisene i ulike grupper", {nextBalise},_ok else return "Feil i beregning av avstand",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseDistanceToPreviousBalise()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks distance to previous balise (lower mileage)
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseDistanceToPreviousBalise() previousBalise = getDownObject(RCType) if (previousBalise == nil) then return "Ingen baliser i kjørbar forbindelse i synkende km", _ok end dist = math.abs(distance(previousBalise)) distOut = string.format("%.3f", dist) if (dist < 2.35 ) then return distOut..": Ugyldig - Balisenes magnetfelt kan flyte sammen – øk avstand", {previousBalise},_error elseif (dist >= 2.35 and dist < 2.8) then return distOut..": Advarsel – Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – øk avstand", {previousBalise},_warning elseif (dist >= 2.8 and dist < 3.2) then return distOut..": OK – Toget vil med god margin plassere balisene i samme gruppe", {previousBalise},_ok elseif (dist >= 3.2 and dist < 3.5) then return distOut..": Advarsel – Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – senk avstand", {previousBalise},_warning elseif (dist >= 3.5 and dist < 10.5) then return distOut..": Ugyldig – Toget kan ikke entydig avgjøre balisenes gruppetilhørighet", {previousBalise},_error elseif (dist >= 10.5 and dist < 11.8) then return distOut..": Advarsel - Tillatt, men utenfor anbefalt byggetoleranse – øk avstand", {previousBalise},_warning elseif (dist > 11.8) then return distOut..": OK – Toget vil med god margin plassere balisene i ulike grupper", {previousBalise}, _ok else return "Feil i beregning av avstand",_warning end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseDistanceToTrackVertically()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks distance to track above or below balise
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseDistanceToTrackVertically() if (Alignment == nil) then return "Balise mangler alignment", _noSymbol end local nearestAlignments = getClosestAlignments() local nearestId = "" local i = 0 while (nearestAlignments[i]) do -- Consider only other alignments being no more than 5 meter sideways apart from balise local aId = nearestAlignments[i].id if (Alignment.id ~= aId and math.abs(getAlignmentInfo(aId).DistanceToAlignment) <= 5.0) then nearestId = aId break else i = i + 1 end end if (nearestId == "") then return "Ingen andre spor innenfor 5 meter sideveis", _ok end local distance = math.abs(getAlignmentInfo().Elevation - getAlignmentInfo(nearestId).Elevation) if (distance <= 0.8) then -- Assume that closest other track is part of a point or crossing, but still accept 80 cm difference for diverging track profiles return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balisen ligger nær et annet spor, men som antas å være i samme plan", _ok elseif (distance > 0.8 and distance <= 7.0) then return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise er for nær annet spor i høyden, øk vertikal sporavstand eller flytt balisen",_error elseif (distance <= 8.0) then return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise er utenfor anbefalt toleranse for sporavstand i høyden, øk vertikal sporavstand eller flytt balisen",_warning else return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise med god margin innenfor sikkerhetskrav for sporavstand i høyden", _ok end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_baliseDistanceToTrackSideways()
LuaFunction.Description: Checks distance from balise to neighbor tracks
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_baliseDistanceToTrackSideways() if (Alignment == nil) then return "Balise mangler alignment", _noSymbol end local nearestAlignments = getClosestAlignments() local nearestId = "" local i = 0 while (nearestAlignments[i]) do if (Alignment.id ~= nearestAlignments[i].id) then nearestId = nearestAlignments[i].id break else i = i+1 end end if (nearestId == "") then return "Ingen nabospor", _ok end local distance = math.abs(getAlignmentInfo(nearestId).DistanceToAlignment) if NOBN_isNan(distance) then return "Kunne ikke beregne avstand til nabospor", _noSymbol end if (distance < 2.0) then return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise innenfor sikkerhetsavstand til nabospor, øk avstand",_error elseif (distance > 2.0 and distance < 2.6) then return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise innenfor sikkerhetskrav til nabospor, men utenfor anbefalt toleranse. Øk avstand",_warning else return string.format("%.3f",distance)..": Balise med god margin innenfor sikkerhetskrav til nabospor", _ok end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_objectLiftWithCant()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns Z-coordinate which is consistent with cant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_objectLiftWithCant() local h = getAlignmentInfo().cant / 1000.0 if NOBN_isNan(h) then return 0,_warning else -- Axle counters are expected to be mounted in one or the other rail, lifted by the superelevation -- It doesn't matter if the cant rotation is clockwise or counterclockwise, but it DOES matter -- whether the axle counter is mounted in a rail that will be lifted with cant or not. cr = tostring(getAlignmentInfo().CantRotation) if cr == "cw" then -- Right curve: Right rail stays at constant height, positive cant lifts left rail return h/2 - h * DistanceToAlignment / NOBN_railSeparation() elseif cr == "ccw" then return h/2 + h * (DistanceToAlignment / NOBN_railSeparation()) end end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_objectRotation3DX()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns pitch-rotation which is consistent with alignment gradient.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_objectRotation3DX() --Pitch (gradient) angle = getAlignmentInfo().gradient if (NOBN_isNan(angle)) then return 0,_warning else return math.atan(angle/1000.0)*(180.0/math.pi) end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_objectRotation3DY()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns roll-rotation which is consistent with cant.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_objectRotation3DY() --Roll (cant) c = getAlignmentInfo().Cant if (NOBN_isNan(c)) then return 0,_warning elseif c == 0 then return 0 else -- Cant is measured in millimeter superelevation, with rotation clockwise or counterclockwise in the track's direction -- Assume that only one rail is lifted at a time. cr = tostring(getAlignmentInfo().CantRotation) if cr:upper() == "CW" then return math.asin(c/1500.0)*(180.0/math.pi) elseif cr:upper() == "CCW" then return -math.asin(c/1500.0)*(180.0/math.pi) else return 90,_warning -- Show that cant rotation is bad end end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_snap()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a snap distance being a multiple of s. Default snap distance is 3, default snap zone starts at 0.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_snap(s) local d if s == nil then s = 3 end s = math.floor(math.abs(s)) if s == 0 then return 0 else d = s * math.floor((0.5 + getAlignmentInfo().DistanceToAlignment) / s) return d end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_km()

LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_km(x,p) if p == nil then p = 3 end p = math.floor(math.abs(p)) if p < 0 or p > 6 then return "Precision ["..p.."] must be from 0 to 6, cannot format value ["..x.."]",_warning elseif p == 0 then return string.format("%.0f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e3)*1e-3)/1e0) elseif p == 1 then return string.format("%.1f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e2)*1e-2)/1e1) elseif p == 2 then return string.format("%.2f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e1)*1e-1)/1e2) elseif p == 3 then return string.format("%.3f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e0)*1e0)/1e3) elseif p == 4 then return string.format("%.4f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-1)*1e1)/1e4) elseif p == 5 then return string.format("%.5f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-2)*1e2)/1e5) elseif p == 6 then return string.format("%.6f",math.floor((x+0.5*1e-3)*1e3)/1e6) end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_spormiddel()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns the reference mileage for the fouling point being farthest from the stock rail joint
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_spormiddel(v) if v == nil then v = this end if v.RCType ~= "KO-SPV Sporveksel" then return "Bad object type ["..RCType.."], 'KO-SPV Sporveksel' was expected" else local fp,dmax,w,i,d fp = getFoulingPoints(v) dmax = 0 w = nil for i = 0,fp.count-1 do -- OLD: d = math.abs(v.ReferenceMileage - fp[i].Branch1.ReferenceMileage) d = math.sqrt((fp[i].FoulingPoint.x - this.geocoord.x)^2 + (fp[i].FoulingPoint.y - this.geocoord.y)^2) if d > dmax then dmax = d w = fp[i].Branch1.ReferenceMileage end end if dmax == 0 then return "(no fouling points found)" else return w end end end

LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_spormiddelEgetSpor(v) if v == nil then v = this end if v.RCType ~= "KO-SPV Sporveksel" then return "Bad object type ["..RCType.."], 'KO-SPV Sporveksel' was expected" else local fp,dmax,w,i,d fp = getFoulingPoints(v) dmax = 0 w = nil for i = 0,fp.count-1 do d = math.abs(v.ReferenceMileage - fp[i].Branch1.ReferenceMileage) --Search for farthest FP using reference track mileage if d > dmax then dmax = d w = fp[i].Branch1.Mileage --Storing OWN ALIGNMENT mileage end end if dmax == 0 then return "(no fouling points found)" else return w end end end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_tableSort()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a sorted table (indexed 1,2,...)
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_tableSort(t) if type(t) ~= type({}) then return '***',_warning end --Insertion sort local u,v,n,i,j,k,lo u = {} v = {} n = 0 while t[n+1] ~= nil do n = n + 1 table.insert(u,t[n]) end for i = 1, n do lo = math.huge for j = 1, n-i+1 do if u[j] < lo then lo = u[j] k = j end end table.insert(v,table.remove(u,k)) --insert smallest number from u into v end return v end

LuaFunction.Name: NOBN_romningsSkiltTekstVH()
LuaFunction.Description: Returns a table {'Left'=Lval,'Right'=Rval} with distance to nearest related marker. Default step 10, default offset 0. '?':missing marker, '+':multiple markers found.
LuaFunction.Formula: function NOBN_romningsSkiltTekstVH(step,offset) local r,n,s,t,i,k,downIndex,upIndex if step == nil then step = 10 else step = math.floor(math.abs(step)) if step == 0 then step = 10 end end if offset == nil then offset = 0 end if this.RCType ~= "KO-SKT Rømningsavstand" then return "Bad object type ["..RCType.."], 'KO-SKT Rømningsavstand' was expected" else r = Relations["Har markør"] n = getCollectionLength(r) s = {} t = {} for i = 1, n do table.insert(t,r[i-1].Mileage) --collection r is indexed from 0 end t = NOBN_tableSort(t) k = 0 for i = 1, n do if Mileage > t[i] then k = k + 1 end end if leftSided then downIndex = "Left" upIndex = "Right" else downIndex = "Right" upIndex = "Left" end if k == 0 then s[downIndex] = "?" elseif k == 1 then s[downIndex] = math.floor((offset + Mileage - t[k] + step/2)/step)*step elseif k >= 1 then s[downIndex] = math.floor((offset + Mileage - t[k] + step/2)/step)*step.."+" end if k == n then s[upIndex] = "?" elseif k == n-1 then s[upIndex] = math.floor(offset + (t[k+1] - Mileage + step/2)/step)*step elseif k <= n-2 then s[upIndex] = math.floor(offset + (t[k+1] - Mileage + step/2)/step)*step.."+" end end return s end

LuaExpression.Name: Variant
LuaExpression.Formula:
alignmentInfo = getAlignmentInfo() nearest = alignmentInfo.NearestHorizontalVertex nearestCant = alignmentInfo.NearestCantVertex
-- insert "RE,RB" if cant station is closest vertexMileage = nearest.Item1 ~= nil and nearest.Item1.EndMileage or nearest.Item2.StartMileage if nearestCant ~= null and math.abs(nearestCant.Mileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) < math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) and math.abs(vertexMileage - alignmentInfo.Mileage) > 1 then if math.abs(nearestCant.GradientIn) > 0 and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientOut) > 0 then return "REB" elseif (nearestCant.GradientIn == nil or nearestCant.GradientIn == 0) and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientOut) > 0 then return "RB" elseif ( nearestCant.GradientOut == nil or nearestCant.GradientOut == 0) and math.abs(nearestCant.GradientIn) > 0 then return "RE" end end
if nearest == nil then return "" end
if nearest.Item1 ~= null and nearest.Item1.Type == "Curve" then if nearest.Item2 == nil or nearest.Item2.Type == "Straight" then return "KP" end if nearest.Item2.Type == "Curve" then return "FKP" end end
if nearest.Item2 ~= null and nearest.Item2.Type == "Curve" then if nearest.Item1 == nil or nearest.Item1.Type == "Straight" then return "KP" end end
if nearest.Item1 ~= null and nearest.Item1.Type == "Clothoid" then if nearest.Item2 ~= null and nearest.Item2.Type == "Clothoid" then if nearest.Item1.RadiusStart < nearest.Item1.RadiusEnd then return "FOB" else return "FOE" end end if nearest.Item1.RadiusStart < nearest.Item1.RadiusEnd then return "OB" else return "OE" end end

-- EH-UTL@DistanceToAlignment.lua (NO-BN) -- (c) Railcomplete AS, 2017, agent NO-0001 -- 2017-01-15 EIKJE: Adjusted variants for Hengemaster -- 2017-06-12 EIKJE: Fixed tan-factor for B- and H-mast. if (getCollectionLength(Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"]) == 0) then --If cantilever has no connection to a mast, then snap to alignment (a visible engineering fault): return RightSided and 0.0001 or -0.0001 else if (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Alignment==nil) then --No alignment available...: return RightSided and 0.0001 or -0.0001 else --Alignment available mv = Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Variant mp = Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Masteprofil if (mv == "Bjelkemast, ny" or mv == "Bjelkemast, eksisterende") then d = string.sub(mp,4,6)/2000 --Assume mast profile names "HEB200", "HEB220" etc elseif (mv == "B-mast, eksisterende") then d = (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Hoyde - RelativeElevation) * math.tan(23/1000000) elseif (mv == "H-mast, eksisterende") then d = (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Hoyde - RelativeElevation) * math.tan(1/50000) elseif (mv == "Hengemast i tunnel, eksisterende" or mv == "Hengemast i tunnel, ny" or mv == "Ny hengemast i åk type 12" or mv == "Ny hengemast i åk type 14" or mv == "Ny hengemast i åk type 40" or mv == "Hengemast Cariboni, ny" or mv == "Hengemast Cariboni, eksisterende") then if (mp == 'Sirkulær, Ø120') then d = 0.06 elseif (mp == 'Kvadratisk, 100x100') then d = 0.05 elseif (mp == 'Rektangulær, 150x100') then d = 0.075 elseif (mp == 'Rektangulær, 200x100') then d = 0.1 else return 0,_warning end else return 0,_warning end end if (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].RightSided) then if (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Alignment.name == Alignment.name) then return Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].DistanceToAlignment - d else return (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].DistanceToAlignment - d)*-1 end else if (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].Alignment.name == Alignment.name) then return Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].DistanceToAlignment + d else return (Relations["Tilhører kl-mast"][0].DistanceToAlignment + d)*-1 end end end
